    h2 History of Video Games
    p Video games have come a long way since their inception in the 1950s. From early arcade machines to home consoles, and now to mobile devices, video games have evolved into one of the most popular forms of entertainment worldwide.
    
    p In the 1970s, arcade games like Pong and Space Invaders became hugely popular. The 1980s saw the rise of home consoles with iconic games like Pac-Man and Super Mario Bros. As technology advanced, the 1990s brought 3D graphics and more immersive gameplay experiences. Today, video games are part of a global culture with eSports, virtual reality, and millions of players worldwide.

    h2 Featured Game Clips
